[h4 id=McbobxSComments 
	" McBobX's comments
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"First off, I'm very happy that I have been part of this project. Since my old 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext="Zero 100%"|href=/5299S)
	" submission, I have always been wanting to participate in a Mega Man X4 project, as it is one of my favorite games of all time. HappyLee offered me this opportunity and guess what, he was above my expectations. His ability to find extra small details I'm not aware of was always surprising and exciting too. I'm glad I worked with a TAS Legend.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=HappyleeSComments 
	" HappyLee's comments
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"I'm honored to work with McBobX on this project. I had no X4 Zero TAS experience when I started the project in 2024. McBobX is more experienced in Mega Man TASing than I am.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I did every input, and found most of the improvements myself. McBobX helped me examine everything along the way. His help with DG-42L (Slash Beast mid-boss) fight was crucial, because back then I was losing hope about saving the train framerule in that stage, and his method inspired me a lot.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Special thanks to 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Bernka 
		"Bernka
	]a
	", Atma & FractalFusion for their previous work on X4 Zero TAS. I grew up watching their TASes, always admired them, and now I've become a top X4 TASer myself.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This could be my last Mega Man X4 long project. I'm planning to update my "X, no items" in the future.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Hope you enjoy watching this run. Feel free to leave comments. If anyone finds an improvement one day, please let me know, and maybe we'll work on it together.
	$LF
]div
